WITH initial_complete AS (
  SELECT 
    kanban_column.order AS last_column,
    SUM(kanban_day.count) AS complete_at_point_zero
  FROM
    kanban_day
    JOIN kanban_column
        ON kanban_day.column_id = kanban_column.id
    JOIN kanban_board
        ON kanban_column.board_id = kanban_board.id
    JOIN kanban_class_of_service
        ON kanban_day.class_of_service_id = kanban_class_of_service.id
    WHERE
        {{ board }}
        [[ AND {{ date }} ]]
        [[ AND {{ class_of_service }} ]]
    GROUP BY kanban_column.order, kanban_day.date
    ORDER BY kanban_column.order DESC, kanban_day.date
    LIMIT 1
)

SELECT 
    kanban_day.date,
    kanban_column.name AS column_name,
    CASE WHEN (kanban_column.order = last_column) THEN SUM(kanban_day.count) - MIN(complete_at_point_zero)
         ELSE SUM(kanban_day.count) END
         AS count
FROM 
    kanban_day
    JOIN kanban_column
        ON kanban_day.column_id = kanban_column.id
    JOIN kanban_board
        ON kanban_column.board_id = kanban_board.id
    JOIN kanban_class_of_service
        ON kanban_day.class_of_service_id = kanban_class_of_service.id
    CROSS JOIN initial_complete
WHERE
    extract(dow from kanban_day.date) = 0
    AND {{ board }}
    [[ AND {{ date }} ]]
    [[ AND {{ class_of_service }} ]]
    
GROUP BY 1, 2, kanban_column.order, last_column
ORDER BY kanban_column.order DESC;

WITH kanban_data AS (
    SELECT 
        *,
        kanban_class_of_service.name as class_of_service
    FROM
        kanban_card
        LEFT JOIN kanban_card_time
            ON kanban_card.id = kanban_card_time.card_id
        JOIN kanban_board
            ON kanban_board.id = kanban_card.board_id
        LEFT JOIN kanban_class_of_service
            ON kanban_card.class_of_service_id = kanban_class_of_service.id
    WHERE 
        {{ board }} 
        AND {{ timing_type }} 
        [[ AND {{ start_date }} ]]
        [[ AND {{ class_of_service }} ]]
)

SELECT
    card_id,
    start_date,
    end_date,
    time,
    class_of_service
FROM 
    kanban_data
ORDER BY start_date

WITH kanban_data AS (
    SELECT 
        * 
    FROM
        kanban_card
        LEFT JOIN kanban_card_time
            ON kanban_card.id = kanban_card_time.card_id
        JOIN kanban_board
            ON kanban_board.id = kanban_card.board_id
        LEFT JOIN kanban_class_of_service
            ON kanban_card.class_of_service_id = kanban_class_of_service.id
    WHERE 
        {{ board }} 
        AND {{ timing_type }} 
        [[ AND {{ start_date }} ]]
        [[ AND {{ class_of_service }} ]]
)

SELECT 
    start_date,
    (SELECT percentile_cont(0.80) within group (order by time asc) FROM kanban_data) AS "80th",
    (SELECT percentile_cont(0.90) within group (order by time asc) FROM kanban_data) AS "90th",
    (SELECT percentile_cont(0.95) within group (order by time asc) FROM kanban_data) AS "95th"
FROM
    kanban_data;

    AVG(count)
FROM (
    SELECT
        TO_CHAR(kanban_card_time.end_date, 'IW-YYYY') AS week,
        COUNT(distinct kanban_card.id) AS count
    FROM 
        kanban_card
        LEFT JOIN kanban_card_time
            ON kanban_card.id = kanban_card_time.card_id
        JOIN kanban_board
            ON kanban_board.id = kanban_card.board_id

    WHERE
        {{ board }}
